# Ignore development files when deploying to Aliyun FC
/node_modules
/src
/public
/client
.git
.gitignore
.fcignore
*.log
/server/.env
/server/node_modules
# Note: server/node_modules will be installed on Aliyun FC build stage if using build,
# or we can upload it if we don't ignore it. Usually we ignore server/node_modules
# and use FC's pre-compilation, or we upload it. Since it's light, we can let FC build it or upload it.
# Let's ignore it and run npm install during build, or we can upload it if it's small.
# Actually, not ignoring server/node_modules is safer if they deploy directly without online build.
# Let's not ignore server/node_modules so it uploads the pre-installed modules, making deployment zero-build.
# So we only ignore the root /node_modules.
